                <p>כךם ל<unclear>דרו</unclear>ם<lb/>שלמ<unclear>י</unclear> ויעולון</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Vineyard belonging to DRWM (or: vineyard [facing] the south)<lb/>ŠLMY and
                    YʽWLWN</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>While Shalmai is known to us both from the Bible and from a Hebrew soapstone
                    steal from the Persian period, the second name (יעולון) is unknown. Perhaps it
                    is related to the Biblical יעואל/יעיאל a derivative of the Arabic root for
                    'gather, collect,' or from על"ל the Aramaic root for 'to enter, to bring
                    in'.</p>
            </div>
